THIS WORKFLOW

- Functionality is grouped into stacks. The stacks are then chained.
- There is a bus/pipe across the top for passing the most common inputs across.
- Node sizes are (should be) multiples of 512x64.


PROBLEMS

Sometimes modified latents get stuck... you then have to poke the <Latent From Batch> node to make it update.

Using "Conditioning (Combine)" even with empty input can cause changes. It also seems to cause noise problems.

A1111 CLIP text encoding doesn't interact properly with <Latent From Batch>. You'll get different images if you try to select within a batch.

"CLIP Text Encode++" isn't _exactly_ the same as "CLIP Text Encode" even when set to 'Comfy' (saw image changes).


QUALITY

Too many steps => too sharp => bad results
Too high config => burned image => bad results


COLOUR SCHEMES

embedding:CS-BBz  - bronzy blues
embedding:CS-BRYO - retro primaries
embedding:CS-CYBR - cyberpunk
embedding:CS-OBG  - neutral orange
embedding:CS-PYS  - purple-yellow metallic
embedding:CS-RBW  - red, black and white
embedding:CS-YBF  - kill bill
